7 The Rahbar is the commanderinchief of the armed forces controls the military intelligence and security operations and has sole power to declare war or peace.299 The heads of the judiciary the state radio and television networks the commanders of the police and military forces and six of the twelve members of the Guardian Council are directly appointed by the Rahbar.299 The Assembly of Experts is responsible for electing the Rahbar and has the power to dismiss him on the basis of qualifications and popular esteem.308 To date the Assembly of Experts has not challenged any of the Rahbars decisions nor attempted to dismiss him.309 The previous head of the judicial system Sadeq Larijani appointed by the Rahbar said that it is illegal for the Assembly of Experts to supervise the Rahbar.310 Many believe the Assembly of Experts has become a ceremonial body without any real power.311312313 President Main article President of Iran Iranian President Ebrahim Raisi with Russian President Vladimir Putin and Turkish President Recep Tayyip Erdoan at the Sadabad Palace in Tehran.314 After the Supreme Leader the Constitution defines the president as the highest state authority.299315 The President is elected by universal suffrage for a term of four years but is required to gain the Leaders official approval before being sworn in before the Parliament. The Leader also has the power to dismiss the elected president.316 The President can only be reelected for one term.315 The President is responsible for the implementation of the constitution and for the exercise of executive powers in implementing the decrees and general policies as outlined by the Rahbar except for matters directly related to the Rahbar which has the final say.299 The procedures for presidential election and all other elections in Iran are outlined by the Rahbar.317 The President functions as the executive of affairs such as signing treaties and other international agreements and administering national planning budget and state employment affairs all as approved by the Rahbar.318319303 The President appoints the ministers subject to the approval of the Parliament as well as the approval of the Rahbar who can dismiss or reinstate any of the ministers at any time.320321322 The President supervises the Council of Ministers coordinates government decisions and selects government policies to be placed before the legislature.323 Eight Vice Presidents serve under the President as well as a cabinet of twentytwo ministers who must all be approved by the legislature.324 Guardian Council Main article Guardian Council Presidential candidates and parliamentary candidates must be approved by the 
12 member Guardian Council all members of which are directly or indirectly appointed by the Leader or the Leader before running to ensure their allegiance.325 The Leader very rarely does the vetting himself directly but has the power to do so in which case additional approval of the Guardian Council would not be needed. The Leader can also revert the decisions of the Guardian Council.326 The Guardian Council can and has dismissed elected members of the parliament.327328 Supreme National Security Council Main article Supreme National Security Council The Supreme National Security Council SNSC is at the top of Irans foreign policy decisions process.329330331 The council was formed during the 1989 Iranian constitutional referendum for the protection and support of national interests the revolution territorial integrity and national sovereignty of the country.332 It is mandated by Article 176 of the Constitution to be presided over by the president.333334 The Supreme Leader selects the secretary of the Supreme council and the decisions of the Council are effective after the confirmation by the Supreme Leader. The SNSC also formulates the countrys nuclear policy and would become effective if they are confirmed by the Supreme Leader.335336 Legislature Main article Islamic Consultative Assembly See also Specialized Commissions of the Parliament of Iran Supreme Audit Court of Iran and Majlis Research Center The Islamic Consultative Assembly also known as the Iranian Parliament The legislature of Iran known as the Islamic Consultative Assembly is a unicameral body comprising 290 members elected for fouryear terms.337 It drafts legislation ratifies international treaties and approves the national budget. All parliamentary candidates and all legislation from the assembly must be approved by the Guardian Council.338 The Guardian Council comprises twelve jurists including six appointed by the Rahbar. Others are elected by the Parliament from among the jurists nominated by the Head of the Judiciary.339340 The Council interprets the constitution and may veto the Parliament. If a law is deemed incompatible with the constitution or Sharia Islamic law it is referred back to the Parliament for revision.315 The Expediency Council has the authority to mediate disputes between the Parliament and the Guardian Council and serves as an advisory body to the Rahbar making it one of the most powerful governing bodies in the country.341 Local city councils are elected by public vote to fouryear terms. Law Main article Judicial system of the Islamic Republic of Iran Relief of Anushiruwan at the Courthouse of Tehran. The Supreme Leader appoints the head of the Supreme Court and the chief public prosecutor.309 There are several types of courts including public courts that deal with civil and criminal cases and revolutionary courts which deal with certain categories of offences such as crimes against national security. The decisions of the revolutionary courts are final and cannot be appealed.309 The Chief Justice is the head of the judicial system and is responsible for its administration and supervision. He is also the highest judge of the Supreme Court of Iran. The Chief Justice nominates some candidates for serving as minister of justice and then the President select one of them. The Chief Justice can serve for two fiveyear terms.342 The Special Clerical Court handles crimes allegedly committed by clerics although it has also taken on cases involving laypeople. The Special Clerical Court functions independently of the regular judicial framework and is accountable only to the Rahbar. The Courts rulings are final and cannot be appealed.309 The Assembly of Experts which meets for one week annually comprises 86 virtuous and learned clerics elected by adult suffrage for eightyear terms. Foreign relations Main article Foreign relations of Iran Nations with which Iran has diplomatic relations. Iran maintains diplomatic relations with 165 countries but not with the United States and not with Israela state which Iran has derecognised since 19
79.3 43 Among Muslim nations Iran has an adversarial relationship with Saudi Arabia due to different political and ideologies. Iran and Turkey have long been at odds historically and involved in modern proxy conflicts such as those in Syria Libya and the South Caucasus.344345346 However they also have shared common interests in some instances such as the issue of Kurdish separatism and the Qatar diplomatic crisis.347348 Iran has a close and strong relationship with Tajikistan often described as one spirit in two bodies due to both being Persianspeaking and Iranic countries.349350351352353 Iran has deep economic relations and alliance with Iraq Lebanon and Syria with Syria often described as Irans closest ally.354355356 The building of Ministry of Foreign Affairs which extensively uses Achaemenid architecture in its facade National Garden Tehran. Russia is a key trading partner of Iran especially in regard to the formers excess oil reserves.357358 Both nations share a close economic and military alliance and are subject to heavy sanctions by most Western nations.359360361362 Iran is the only country in Western Asia that has been invited to join the Collective Security Treaty Organization the Russiabased international treaty organization that parallels NATO.363 Relations between Iran and China is strong both bilaterally and economically. They have developed a friendly economic and strategic relationship. In March 2021 Iran and China signed a 
25 year cooperation agreement that will strengthen the relations between the two countries and would include political strategic and economic components.364 IranChina relations dates back to at least 200 BC and possibly earlier.365366 Iran is one of the few countries in the world that has a good relationship with both North and South Korea.367 Iran is a member of dozens of international organizations including the G15 G24 G77 IAEA IBRD IDA NAM IDB IFC ILO BRI IMF IMO Interpol OIC OPEC WHO and the United Nations and currently has observer status at the World Trade Organization. Military Main articles Military history of Iran and Islamic Republic of Iran Armed Forces MRBM Sejjil. Iran is the worlds 
6 th missile power and the 
5 th country in the world with hypersonic missile technology. The Iranian military is organized under a unified structure the Islamic Republic of Iran Armed Forces comprising the Islamic Republic of Iran Army Artesh which includes the Ground Forces Air Defence Force Air Force and Navy the Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps Sepah which consists of the Ground Forces Aerospace Force Navy Quds Force and Basij and the Law Enforcement Force Faraja which serves an analogous function to a gendarme. While the IRIAF protects the countrys sovereignty in a traditional capacity the IRGC is mandated to ensure the integrity of the Islamic Republic principally against foreign interference coups and internal riots.368 Since 1925 it is mandatory for all male citizen aged 18 to serve around 14 months in the IRIAF or the IRGC.369370371372 Iran has over 610000 active troops and around 350000 reservists totalling over 1 million trained military personnel one of the worlds highest percentage of citizens with military training.373374375376 The Basij a paramilitary volunteer militia within the IRGC has over 20 million members 600000 members available for immediate callup 300000 reservists and a million that could be mobilized when necessary.377378379380 Faraja the Iranian uniformed police force has over 260000 active personnel. Most statistical organizations do not include the Basij and Faraja in their ratings report. Excluding the Basij and Faraja Iran has been identified as a major military power owing it to the size and capabilities of its armed forces. It possesses the worlds 
14 th strongest military.381 It ranks 
13 th globally in terms of overall military strength382 
7 th in the number of active military personnel382 and 
9 th in the size of both its ground force and armoured force. Irans armed forces are the largest in West Asia and comprise the greatest Army Aviation fleet in the Middle East.383384385 Iran is among the top 15 countries in terms of military budget.386 In 2021 its military spending increased for the first time in four years to 
24.6  billion 
2.3 0 of the national GDP.387 Funding for the IRGC accounted for 34 of Irans total military spending in 20
