3.6 754676 Health Main article Healthcare in Iran Razavi Hospital accredited by ACI for its quality Health Services677 Healthcare is provided by the publicgovernmental system the private sector and NGOs.678 The country faces the common problem of other young demographic nations in the region which is keeping pace with growth of an already huge demand for various public services. An anticipated increase in the population growth rate will increase the need for public health infrastructures and services.679 About 90 of Iranians have some form of health insurance.680 Iran is the only country in the world with a legal organ trade.681 Iran has been able to extend public health preventive services through the establishment of an extensive Primary Health Care Network. As a result child and maternal mortality rates have fallen significantly and life expectancy at birth has risen. Irans medical knowledge rank is 
17 th globally and 
1 st in the Middle East and North Africa. In terms of medical science production index Iran ranks 
16 th in the world.682 Iran is fast emerging as a preferred destination for medical tourism.563564 Religion Main article Religion in Iran Iranian people by religion 2011 General Census Results683 Note other groups are officially excluded Religion Percent Number Muslim 
